{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside. Place ham into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>Turbo\/0.5 sec\/0 times<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place hard-boiled eggs into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to another bowl and set aside.","Place olive oil, butter and onion into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>3 min\/250°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add flour and sauté <nobr>3 min\/250°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add milk, nutmeg, salt and pepper and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>.","Add 2 tbsp reserved chopped ham and cook <nobr>8 min\/250°F\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Let mixture rest for 5 minutes. Add remaining ham and chopped eggs and mix <nobr>45 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>, stir through with spatula.","Transfer béchamel mixture into a bowl, cover with foil or cling wrap pushed down on top of the béchamel to avoid forming a skin and allow to cool for 20 minutes before placing into a piping bag. Pipe béchamel with largest piping tip into 5 equal lengths (approx. 15 in. x 1 in.) onto prepared baking sheet and refrigerate for 8 hours minimum or overnight.","Cut cold béchamel strips into croquettes (approx. 1½ in.), dip in whisked eggs and roll through bread crumbs. Fry each croquette in oil until brown on all sides, allow to drain on paper towels and serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["5 ½ oz Black Forest ham, cubed (1 in.)","2 hard-boiled eggs","2 oz extra virgin olive oil","3 ½ oz unsalted butter, room temperature","1 oz yellow onion","6 oz all-purpose flour","27 oz whole milk, room temperature","1 pinch ground nutmeg","¼ tsp salt, to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper","3 large eggs, whisked","7 oz bread crumbs","olive oil, to fry"]}],"id":"r212623","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-_LtDGLw3KS8\/XZMtzPbqIuI\/AAAAAAAAZ9k\/mZskYEmZo08cHEM2I_EkJviGCaFWLvnXwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1BYf-7lw5uAdKVoX.png","title":"Ham and Béchamel Croquettes","publishedAt":"2017-08-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.64 g","fat":"6.07 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"5.64 g","calories":"367 kJ \/ 88 kcal"},"usefulItems":"deep frying pan, paper towels, baking sheet, parchment paper, piping bag with large tip (approx. 1 in.), aluminum foil or cling wrap, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Scissors can be used to cut chilled bechamel into 1½ inch pieces. Use a fork to help run pieces through egg and bread crumbs before frying.","Use a deep fryer for best results.","If a piping bag is unavailable cut one of the corners off a zip lock bag, fill the baggie with bechamel and pipe onto baking sheet."],"basicInfo":["advanced","30m","9h 50m","50 pieces"]}